crochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_XXL_backside-3x.a7347a09.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=2000 2000w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_XXL_backside-3x.a7347a09.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=2600 2600w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_XXL_backside-3x.a7347a09.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=3200 3200w" sizes="100vw"/><source media="screen and (min-width: 980px)" srcSet="https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_large_backside-3x.cd457447.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=200 200w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_large_backside-3x.cd457447.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=800 800w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_large_backside-3x.cd457447.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=1400 1400w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_large_backside-3x.cd457447.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=2000 2000w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_large_backside-3x.cd457447.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=2600 2600w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_large_backside-3x.cd457447.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=3200 3200w" sizes="100vw"/><img class="vs-image" srcSet="https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_mid_backside-3x.7513c450.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=200 200w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_mid_backside-3x.7513c450.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=800 800w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_mid_backside-3x.7513c450.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=1400 1400w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_mid_backside-3x.7513c450.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=2000 2000w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_mid_backside-3x.7513c450.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=2600 2600w, https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fig.ft.com%2Fmicrochips%2Fassets%2Fstatic%2Fg1702_23X_backside_power_mid_backside-3x.7513c450.png?source=ig&amp;quality=high&amp;width=3200 3200w" src="https://ig.ft.com/microchips/assets/static/g1702_23X_backside_power_mid_backside-3x.7513c450.png" alt="" sizes="100vw"/></picture></figure></div></div><div class="o-grid-container"><div class="o-grid-row"><div data-o-grid-colspan="12 S11 Scenter M9 L8 XL7"><div class="vs-inline-image"><figure class="vs-inline-image__figure"><picture></picture><div class="vs-caption"><figcaption class="vs-caption__caption">Source: Intel</figcaption></div></figure></div></div></div></div></div><div class="o-grid-container"><div class="o-grid-row"><div data-o-grid-colspan="12 S11 Scenter M9 L8 XL7"><div class="body-text o-editorial-layout-wrapper"><p>Alternatives to silicon may also be seen within the decade. High-mobility or 2D materials, such as graphene, which allow electrons to move around quickly, could pave the way for “faster switches” and a leap in capabilities, says Sell.</p><p>“The periodic table has a lot more elements to work with, so there’s plenty of room for us to innovate,” he adds.</p><p>Another emerging field is photonics, where photons, the building blocks of light, are used in place of electrons to carry data at higher speeds. Companies, including TSMC, are currently experimenting.</p><p>Although nothing in chipmaking is ever certain, the accelerating demand for AI, illustrated this month by Nvidia’s bumper results and bullish forecasts, will mean no shortage of incentives for chipmakers to continue increasing computing power.</p><p>“It’s so integral to what we do in our everyday lives and I think we take it for granted,” says Intel’s Auth, reflecting on the leaps in science enabling chip development. “I’m excited to see what we can do over the next 20 years.”</p><p>Cao is equally confident his team of TSMC engineers can continue to be pioneers, developing new generations of chips at a “regular pace” well into the future. The company’s customers demand it.</p><p>“It stops when no one’s asking for it,” he says. “And that is not the case.”</p></div></div></div></div><div class="o-grid-container"><div class="o-grid-row"><div data-o-grid-colspan="12 S11 Scenter M9 L8 XL7"><p style="margin-top:0"><em>This story is free to read so you can share it with family and friends who don’t yet have an FT subscription.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div class="o-grid-container"><div class="o-grid-row"><div data-o-grid-colspan="12 S11 Scenter M9 L8 XL7"><div class="vs-credits"><div class="vs-credits__team"><p> </p><p class="bylines-mobile"><b>Visual storytelling team:</b> <a href="https://ft.com/irene-de-la-torre-arenas">Irene de la Torre Arenas</a>, <a href="https://ft.com/dan-clark">Dan Clark</a>,<!-- --> <a href="https://ft.com/bob-haslett">Bob Haslett</a>, <a href="https://ft.com/sam-joiner">Sam Joiner</a>, <a href="https://ft.com/sam-learner">Sam Learner</a> and <a href="https://ft.com/lucy-rodgers">Lucy Rodgers</a>.</p><p> <!-- -->Additional reporting by<!-- --> <a href="https://www.ft.com/qianer-liu" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Qianer Liu</a>.</p><p>Intel and TSMC consulted on chip manufacturing processes.<!-- --> <a href="https://scaleofuniverse.com/en-gb" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Scale of the Universe</a> <!-- -->and Nikon’s<!-- --> <a href="https://www.nikon.com/company/corporate/sp/universcale/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Universcale</a> <!-- -->provided inspiration for the opening sequence.</p></div><div class="g-share g-share--undefined"><div class="o-share" data-o-component="o-share"><ul><li class="o-share__action"><a class="o-share__icon o-share__icon--twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://ig.ft.com/microchips/&amp;text=Inside the miracle of modern chip manufacturing&amp;via=ft" rel="noopener"><span class="o-share__text">Share on <!-- -->Twitter<!-- -->. Opens in a new window.</span></a></li><li class="o-share__action"><a class="o-share__icon o-share__icon--facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://ig.ft.com/microchips/&amp;t=Inside the miracle of modern chip manufacturing" rel="noopener"><span class="o-share__text">Share on <!-- -->Facebook<!-- -->. Opens in a new window.</span></a></li><li class="o-share__action"><a class="o-share__icon o-share__icon--linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&amp;url=https://ig.ft.com/microchips/&amp;title=Inside the miracle of modern chip manufacturing&amp;source=Financial+Times" rel="noopener"><span class="o-share__text">Share on <!-- -->LinkedIn<!-- -->. Opens in a new window.</span></a></li><li class="o-share__action"><a class="o-share__icon o-share__icon--whatsapp" href="whatsapp://send?text=Inside the miracle of modern chip manufacturing - https://ig.ft.com/microchips/" rel="noopener"><span class=