ical dimensions, it does allude to the shrinking scale of their components. These tiny switches, which control the flow of electrical signals inside every digital device, are the workhorses of microprocessors and the basic building blocks of modern electronics."}]},{"type":"scrolly","steps":[{"step":0,"figure":"start","config":{},"cards":[{"text":"Many advanced transistors are now built atom-by-atom. Some of the smallest are 50nm tall  — and turn on and off billions of times a second."}]},{"step":1,"figure":"bring","config":{},"cards":[{"text":"Their 3D design and shape, unlike their “planar”, or flat, predecessors, allow them to be densely packed."}]},{"step":2,"figure":"show","config":{},"cards":[{"text":"Just one square millimetre can be home to 200 million transistors, with tens of billions across a chip. Manufacturers plan to cram in a trillion in the not-too-distant future."}]},{"step":3,"figure":"bring","config":{},"cards":[{"text":"Ultra-tiny, tightly packed metal wires connect these transistors together, as well as all the other elements that make up the chip’s integrated circuit."}]},{"step":4,"figure":"stack","config":{},"cards":[{"text":"Multiple layers of these interconnects allow different parts of the chip to talk to each other as well as bring in power."}]},{"step":5,"figure":"pull","config":{},"cards":[{"text":"Some chips can contain almost 500km of wiring."}]},{"step":6,"figure":"show","config":{},"cards":[{"text":"Multiple chips are constructed like this across a silicon wafer — the base on which all integrated circuits powering our devices are built."}]},{"step":7,"figure":"zoom","config":{},"cards":[{"text":"A typical 30cm wafer can be home to trillions of transistors . . ."}]},{"step":8,"figure":"continue","config":{},"cards":[{"text":". . . across thousands of individual chips."}]}],"figures":[{"key":"start","config":{},"steps":[0]},{"key":"bring","config":{},"steps":[1]},{"key":"show","config":{},"steps":[2]},{"key":"bring","config":{},"steps